COMMISSIONER OF INTERNAL REVENUE v. ESTATE of Julius B. WEIL, Deceased, Pauling P. Weil, Eugene J. Stern, and M. E. Kilpatrick, Executors. No. 10524. United States Court of Appeals Sixth Circuit Oct. 8, 1948. Sewall Key and J. P. Wenchel, both of Washington, D. C, for petitioner. Marion Smith, Bertram S. Boley, and M. E. Kilpatrick, all of Atlanta, Ga., for respondent.

Before HICKS, Qiief Judge, and ALLEN and MARTIN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Pursuant to motion of respondents it is. ordered that the petition for review be and the same is dismissed for want of prosecution, with leave to petitioner to move for reinstatement upon good cause shown.
